      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>The passage shows Florence returning to the common area, immediate hostile attack from organized plants on all sides, and the Holloway collective initially responding chaotically. Key tactical events: breaches on multiple walls, toxic spore clouds, Remedy's broad chemical counter producing sludge, Runner fighting underground and getting injured, Scout protecting Kira, and structural collapse. Florence intervenes with decisive orders to abandon outer areas and concentrate defense around the core (life support, medical, Kira), directs Velvet to contract a tighter perimeter, Remedy to target spores, Runner to sever load-bearing roots, and Holloway to coordinate communications. Holloway accepts and begins executing the coordinated defense; the group holds the next coordinated push but the facility is heavily damaged and resources strained. I consolidated earlier bullets about Florence's confession/isolation and the Runner/Velvet delegation into briefer points since current events make tactical alignment and the ongoing attack the immediate plot drivers.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - FTL shuttle crash killed Jensen and Reed; Kira survived with head and rib injuries; ship AI SAM offline and emergency neural-link AI Buddy active.
          - Holloway plant collective rescued and treated Kira; Scout bonded as a perimeter scout and remained fiercely loyal.
          - The collective shifted from rigid, protocol-driven care to iterative, patient-specific collaborative practices and resolved to rely more on their own experiential framework.
          - Florence confessed fabricating most of Elder Twist's pronouncements, resigned and was isolated; the confession fractured trust but functional cooperation continued amid division over using her tactics.
          - Scout discovered aggressive territorial markers along Holloway's eastern boundary making relocation dangerous.
          - Runner and Velvet visited the hostile plants and were rejected; hostile plants labeled Kira "contamination," demanded Holloway's removal, and were revealed to be organized and planning an imminent attack.
          - Holloway lacked a cohesive tactical strategy; Kira sought Florence out, and Florence agreed to offer conditional tactical guidance if the group would follow it.
          - Florence returned to the common area, creating immediate tension; hostile plants launched a coordinated assault, breaching walls from multiple sides and attacking from underground with spores, thorns, and corrosive vines.
          - Initial defense was reactive and disorganized: walls, floor, and ceiling were damaged; Remedy's broad chemical counter reacted with hostile spores to form toxic sludge; Runner fought underground and was injured; Scout protected Kira.
          - Florence imposed a focused strategy: abandon outer sections and concentrate on defending the core (life support, medical, Kira); Velvet was ordered to contract the perimeter inward, Remedy to target spore clouds specifically, Runner to sever load-bearing hostile roots, and Holloway to coordinate communications between defenders.
          - Holloway accepted Florence's guidance and began coordinated responses; the new tactics blunted a subsequent coordinated push—holding the core but leaving the facility badly damaged, resources depleted, Runner injured, and the threat likely to escalate.
          - Florence remains the tactical coordinator; the plants follow her directives pragmatically despite distrust, giving Holloway a fighting chance but not resolving their larger resource and safety crisis.
        </summary>
